<TITLE> Stamp duty on village land sales to go up </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 15 (bdnews24.com)  The government on Monday decided to bring parity to the level of stamp duty paid on sales of rural and urban land. According to the decision, stamp duty on the sale of village land will be increased at par with urban areas. "The government has taken the decision to increase the revenue collection from village land sales," said the prime minister's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad at a briefing after a cabinet meeting on Monday. "The duty will be increased from the previous rate of two percent to three percent," Azad said. "As a result, now both the villagers and the city dwellers will have to pay three percent of the total money of the land transfer," the press secretary said. He also said finance minister AMA Muhith would place in parliament on Tuesday the report on the economic development that had taken place in the first half of the 2009-2010 fiscal year. "The cabinet expressed its satisfaction about the present economic situation of the country," he said. The press secretary left the briefing without answering journalists' questions. bd
